Step-by-step reasoning:
- The user wants to turn on the Kitchen Door Porch Light to 75% brightness.
- The trigger is when the device is physically turned on, which is a COC event with command "Fast On" (DFON).
- Upon this COC, the action is to send the On command (DON) with parameter 75% brightness.
- Additionally, set the ramp rate to fast. The fastest ramp rate enum is 0.1 seconds [31].
- So first set ramp rate to 31, then turn on to 75%.
- The device name is "Kitchen Door Porch Light (control)".
- Commands used: Ramp Rate [RR] with parameter 31, then On [DON] with parameter 75.

{
  "routine": {
    "name": "Turn on Kitchen Porch Light at 75% on physical fast on",
    "condition": {
      "==": {
        "device": "Kitchen Door Porch Light (control)",
        "coc": "DFON"
      }
    },
    "actions": [
      {
        "device": "Kitchen Door Porch Light (control)",
        "command": "Ramp Rate",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "RR", "value": 31, "uom": "seconds", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      },
      {
        "device": "Kitchen Door Porch Light (control)",
        "command": "On",
        "parameters": [
          { "name": "", "value": 75, "uom": "%", "precision": 1 }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
